While it’s most likely that he IS linked to their colors, I think it’s at least a distinction to point out.
All faeries are Fey, but not all Fey are faeries when we contextualize it with WOTC.
all squares are rectangles but not not all rectangles are WOTC approved
Elves are Fae in real-world lore, but not always in magic

That’s part of the reason I wanted to at least make the distinction. Seeing Fey used so often rather than Faerie is really one of my two main anchoring point. The other being that Thrones of Eldraine, to me, really invokes the idea of the Seelie Court (and Eldraine being so similar to Eladrin.)
